resign /rɪˈzaɪn/

(resigning,resigned,resigns) 

1. V-T/V-I If you resign from a job or position, you formally announce that you are leaving it. 辞职 

例： A hospital administrator has resigned over claims he lied to get the job. 一位医院主管因为有人声称他的职位是骗来的而辞职了。 

例： Mr Robb resigned his position last month. 罗布先生上个月辞去了他的职位。 

2. V-T If you resign yourself to an unpleasant situation or fact, you accept it because you realize that you cannot change it. 使屈从 

例： Pat and I resigned ourselves to yet another summer without a boat. 帕特和我将就着又过了一个没有船的夏天。 

3.  →  see also resigned

